{"search_data": "Central PM Rojgar Protsahan Yojana (PMRPY) Beneficiaries Now 1 Crore Employees Pradhan Mantri Rojgar Protsahan Yojana beneficiaries number crosses 1 crore on 15 January 2019, labour ministry claims that around 10 million employees joined EPFO via PMRPY & employers incentivized to generate employment opportunities in organized sectorPM Rojgar Protsahan Yojana Reaches 1 Crore EmployeesPradhan Mantri Rozgar Protsahan Yojana (PMRPY) is the scheme to generate new employment opportunities by incentivizing employers and has now reached 1 crore mark. PM Rojgar Protsahan Yojana has dual benefits, on the one hand, employers are incentivized to increase employment base of workers in establishment while on the other hand, a large number of workers will have access to social security benefits of organized sector.PMRPY is the flagship scheme of the central govt. for employment generation and has now crossed the milestone of 1 crore beneficiaries on 14 January 2019. During FY 2016-17 there were 33,031 beneficiaries, for 2017-18 there were 30,27,612 beneficiaries and for 2018-19 there were 69,49,436 beneficiaries (all data upto 15 January 2019) enrolled with EPFO under PMRPY.The total number of establishments which have been benefited during the implementation of PMRPY Scheme is 1.24 lakh. The entire system is now online and aadhaar based with no human interface in the implementation of PM Rozgar Protsahan Yojana.PMRPY scheme offers a direct benefit to workers while providing access to social security benefit through PF, pension and death linked insurance. The last date for beneficiary registration through establishment under PMRPY Scheme is 31 March 2019.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}